<br>
the spell system is kinda hard to get used to, basically you have levels of spells, i think wizards get 9 levels total, my pallie is lvl 8 right now and she has her 2nd level spells now.  and you get these spells automatically depending on how many points you allocate to the skill needed (like my pallie needs to put points into heal and concentration to get more spells) and when you open your spellbook, you get 2 panels.  one is the list of spells available to you, and another is the spells you choose to memorize.  you are limited on the # of spells you can memorize and that's dependant on your level.  example, i have 6 level 1 spells available to me, but i can only memorize 3 of them.  i have 6 level 2 spells available to me, and i can memorize 1 of them.  So I have a total of 4 spells memorized, and hotkeyed.  <br>
<br>
Then you gotta rest for the spells to pop.  You can cast each spell once (for paladin and most classes, as for enchanters and clerics, you have like 5 or 6 charges on each spell) and once you use that spell, it's greyed out, so you have to rest if you want to cast it again.   Once you rest, all your buffs fall off, your summoned pets die (except familiars and creatures which are class specific abilities) and you'll have to rebuff once you're done resting.  <br>
<br>
There is no concept of mana in the game.  You are recharged by &quot;resting&quot; and every time I rest I get my class abilities back too like lay on hands and ward undead (5 charges of AoE damage to undead, such a cool spell) I don't rest a lot as my paladin because all the spells I have memorized are buffs and they don't fall off for a long time, but on my sorc i had to rest a lot and it slows down gameplay (resting takes about 10 seconds) and it got kinda boring.   <p>Trillian GNOME Cleric - Shoeless N00b<br>
